# Proveria V1 Engineering Plan

> **Status:** Incorporates Product / Architecture decisions dated 2026-05-13. See [§30. Decision Log](#30-product--architecture-decision-log--2026-05-13) for the consolidated answers to Engineering's remaining planning questions.

## 1. Executive Summary

Proveria V1 is a desktop-first provenance platform that allows producers to create cryptographic attestations over files and document content without uploading plaintext materials to Proveria.

The core V1 product loop is:

> **Producer pairs desktop app → creates/selects project → selects local files → hashes/shingles locally → signs manifest → uploads cryptographic metadata → Proveria validates → attestation confirms → consumer performs scoped verification → Proveria generates proof/result package and PDF receipt.**

The product must preserve the central trust principle:

> **Proveria does not ingest customer plaintext.**

Hashing, shingling, PDF extraction, and OCR happen locally inside the desktop app. Proveria receives only cryptographic metadata, manifests, Merkle trees, signatures, receipts, proof packages, and audit records. This aligns with the Proveria architectural ledger: local hashing/shingling, no plaintext ingestion, cryptographic receipts, optional blockchain anchoring, and enterprise-grade auditability. 

