# 6. Backend Architecture

## 6.1 Service Split

V1 uses separate services, but not excessive microservices.

| Service        | Responsibility                                                              |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Web portal     | Producer/admin/consumer UI                                                  |
| API service    | Auth, tenancy, devices, projects, attestations, lookup, access grants       |
| Worker service | Validation, proof generation, receipt generation, PDF rendering, audit jobs |
| Database       | Canonical relational app state                                              |
| Object storage | Immutable manifests, receipts, proof bundles, exports                       |
| Queue          | Async job orchestration                                                     |

Architectural posture:

> **Separate deployable processes, shared monorepo, clear boundaries.**

## 6.2 API Framework

Use:

> **Fastify + TypeScript + REST + OpenAPI**

Reasons:

* Lightweight
* Strong schema validation
* Clear REST resource model
* Easier enterprise review
* Better fit for attestations, receipts, proofs, projects, and audit trails
* Easier SDK generation later

No GraphQL in V1.

## 6.3 Pilot Deployment Target

V1 pilot deploys to **AWS, single-region, default `us-east-1`**. Multi-region deployment is deferred to V2 (see §28).

| Component       | Pilot target                                                                  |
| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| App containers  | AWS ECS/Fargate (single EC2 Docker host acceptable as an interim accelerator) |
| Postgres        | RDS Postgres                                                                  |
| Object storage  | S3                                                                            |
| Queue / Redis   | ElastiCache Redis; containerized Redis acceptable for the earliest pilot     |
| Secrets         | AWS Secrets Manager or SSM Parameter Store                                    |
| Transactional email | Resend by default; SES interchangeable behind the notification adapter   |
| Logs            | CloudWatch                                                                    |
| Corp site       | Deployed with the app stack initially; may move to static hosting later       |

Intended production-like path is **ECS/Fargate + RDS + S3 + ElastiCache**. Milestone 1 does not require standing this up — Milestone 1 targets local Docker Compose with MinIO. AWS deployment readiness lands at Milestone 15 (see §26.1).

> **Local dev remains Docker Compose with MinIO. Pilot/production runs on AWS in `us-east-1`.**

