# 10. Project and Template Model

## 10.1 Projects

Projects are tenant-scoped containers for attestations.

V1 project features:

* created from desktop or portal
* private by default for paid tiers
* public-only for Free
* fixed system template selection
* classification/tags
* project-level overrides
* archive/restore by Tenant Admin only
* no hard deletion in V1

Archived projects:

* cannot receive new attestations
* remain visible to admins
* remain verifiable if access remains valid
* retain receipts/proofs/audit history

## 10.2 Fixed System Templates

V1 uses fixed system templates only.

Recommended templates:

| Template               | Use Case                               |
| ---------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| General Provenance     | Default catch-all                      |
| AI Training Corpus     | Model/content provenance               |
| Legal Evidence Package | Litigation/discovery/case files        |
| Research Dataset       | Research materials                     |
| Software Release       | Source archives/binaries/releases      |
| Media Archive          | Image/video/audio/document collections |

No tenant-created or tenant-edited templates in V1.

## 10.3 Overrides

Templates provide defaults.

V1 allows controlled overrides at:

* project level
* attestation level

Allowed override examples:

* project name
* attestation label
* classification
* tags
* terminology overrides
* artifact expectations
* shingling preset, if allowed
* receipt instructions
* verification instructions

Overrides cannot weaken tenant/project/template policy.

