# 11. Attestation Model

## 11.1 Attestation Creation

Producer attestations are desktop-only in V1.

No web upload of source material.

No web upload of manually precomputed manifests in V1.

The desktop wizard is the primary producer workflow.

## 11.2 Attestation Labels

Attestation labels must be unique within a project.

Rules:

* unique per project
* reusable across different projects
* editable while local draft
* not editable once confirmed
* stable internal immutable ID always exists
* labels remain reserved while the attestation record exists, including canceled/failed pre-confirmation attempts

Label release escape hatch:

> **Tenant Admins may release a reserved label from a canceled or failed pre-confirmation attestation.** Confirmed attestations are never eligible. Released labels become reusable within the project. The release action is audit-logged. The original attestation retains its immutable internal ID and historical label record.

## 11.3 Lifecycle States

Recommended V1 states:

```txt
draft_local
uploaded
validation_failed
validated
queued_for_publication
publishing
confirming
confirmed
canceled
failed_needs_review
```

Local-only drafts do not exist as server attestations.

## 11.4 Cancellation and Repair

Rules:

| State                  | Behavior                                      |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Local draft            | Can delete freely                             |
| Uploaded/pre-confirmed | Can cancel                                    |
| Validation failed      | Can repair/resubmit same attestation record   |
| Confirmed              | Immutable; cannot cancel/delete/rename/modify |

Repair/resubmit model:

* stable `attestation_id`
* new `submission_attempt_id` per upload
* failed attempts retained
* final confirmed attempt becomes canonical

## 11.5 Auto Confirmation

After desktop submission:

```txt
uploaded → validation → queued_for_publication → publishing → confirming → confirmed
```

No second approval step after validation.

The desktop wizard review step is the producer approval moment.

