# 14. Server Validation

Server validation includes:

* schema validation
* tenant/project/user permission checks
* device authorization
* device signature verification
* template/policy compliance
* attestation label uniqueness
* plan entitlement checks
* allowed artifact/shingle policy
* hash algorithm/version checks
* deterministic leaf ordering
* duplicate leaf detection
* leaf count consistency
* Merkle root recomputation
* object-store artifact consistency
* receipt/proof package consistency

Boundary:

> **The server does not recompute hashes from plaintext artifacts because Proveria never receives plaintext.**

It validates that the submitted cryptographic metadata is internally consistent, authorized, signed, and policy-compliant.

## 14.1 Merkle Leaf and Node Encoding

Protocol V1 mandates binary-safe, domain-separated leaf and node encoding.

Leaf hash input:

```txt
leaf_hash_input =
  0x00
  || length_prefixed(protocol_version)
  || length_prefixed(leaf_type)
  || length_prefixed(hash_algorithm)
  || length_prefixed(canonical_payload_hash)
```

Internal node hash input:

```txt
node_hash_input =
  0x01
  || left_child_hash
  || right_child_hash
```

Rules:

* leaves are domain-separated from internal nodes via prefix bytes (`0x00` / `0x01`)
* all variable-length components are length-prefixed
* byte order is explicit and documented in the Protocol V1 spec
* odd leaf counts: handling specified in Protocol V1 (default candidate: promote final unpaired hash upward unchanged; alternatives evaluated in the spec draft)
* JSON-embedded hashes use lowercase hex
* no floats in cryptographic payloads

## 14.2 Verifier Versioning

Verifier implementation must dispatch by protocol version:

```txt
protocol_version → verifier implementation
```

Confirmed attestations remain valid under the protocol version they were created with. Verifiers must support all non-revoked historical protocol versions for as long as artifacts under those versions remain valid.

| Scenario                                          | Behavior                                                                              |
| ------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Protocol V1.0 ships                               | V1.0 attestations remain valid under V1.0 rules                                       |
| V1.1 adds non-breaking feature                    | New attestations may use V1.1; old V1.0 remains valid                                 |
| V1.1 fixes minor ambiguity without security issue | Keep V1.0 verifier; mark V1.1 preferred                                               |
| V1.0 has security-impacting flaw                  | Mark V1.0 as legacy/risk-qualified; require explicit verifier warning                 |
| Catastrophic flaw                                 | Disable new V1.0 attestations; preserve historical records with warning/legacy status |

