# 15. Signing Model

## 15.1 Signing Layers

| Signing Type                           | Free | Team | Enterprise |
| -------------------------------------- | ---: | ---: | ---------: |
| Desktop/user/device manifest signature |  Yes |  Yes |        Yes |
| Proveria platform signature            |   No |  Yes |        Yes |
| Customer-managed signing               |   No |   No |   Optional |
| Blockchain anchoring                   |   No |   No |   Optional |

## 15.1.1 V1 Algorithm Posture

| Signing layer                  | V1 algorithm posture                                             |
| ------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Desktop / device manifest      | **Ed25519** (required)                                           |
| Proveria platform signature    | **Ed25519** recommended unless infrastructure requires otherwise |
| Customer-managed signing (Ent.) | Enterprise-configurable; may follow customer KMS/HSM constraints |

Ed25519 is V1's default device-signing algorithm: small keys, fast sign/verify, deterministic signatures, fewer curve-misuse footguns, and good fit for local desktop/device identity. Desktop/device signing is **not** required to be HSM-compatible in V1 — enterprise KMS/HSM concerns are handled separately by the customer-managed signing layer in §15.4.

## 15.2 Desktop Manifest Signing

All desktop submissions are signed by the paired desktop/user/device credential using **Ed25519** (see §15.1.1).

Purpose:

> Proves the manifest came from an authorized paired desktop/user/device for a tenant.

## 15.3 Proveria Signing

Team and Enterprise receipts/result packages are Proveria-signed.

Purpose:

> Proves Proveria validated and issued the receipt/result package.

## 15.4 Customer-Managed Signing

Enterprise optional.

Applies to both:

* attestations
* receipts/result packages

Can later integrate with:

* AWS KMS
* Azure Key Vault
* Google Cloud KMS
* HSMs
* enterprise key systems

