# 16. Consumer Verification and Lookup

## 16.1 Lookup Scope

V1 supports scoped lookup only.

No global hash search. No global searchable registry.

Consumers verify against:

* a specific public Free attestation (reached via direct URL, QR code, or reference ID)
* or a specific private Team/Enterprise attestation they are authorized to access

## 16.2 Private Access

Team/Enterprise private lookup requires:

* consumer login
* explicit authorization
* attestation-specific access grant

An unguessable link alone is not authorization.

Tenant Admins manage consumer access.

Producers cannot invite/authorize consumers.

## 16.3 Pre-Lookup Metadata

Use one fixed conservative metadata policy in V1.

Show before lookup:

| Metadata                    |              Show? |
| --------------------------- | -----------------: |
| Producer organization       |                Yes |
| Project display name        |                Yes |
| Attestation label           |                Yes |
| Confirmation timestamp      |                Yes |
| Coverage type               |                Yes |
| Hash algorithm/version      |                Yes |
| Signature status            |                Yes |
| Blockchain anchoring status | Yes, if applicable |

Hide before lookup:

* artifact count
* shingle count
* file names
* file paths
* full manifest
* excluded/failed file details
* proof paths

## 16.4 Lookup Results

Every lookup generates a durable result package.

Match result includes:

* submitted hash
* matched attestation
* match type
* Merkle proof path
* Merkle root
* signature status
* package reference

No-match result includes:

* submitted hash
* scoped attestation checked
* confirmation timestamp
* Merkle root
* hash algorithm/version
* signed no-match statement
* verification timestamp

Important claim language:

> “This hash was not present in this specific attestation’s committed hash set.”

Never claim universal absence.

