# 27. Recommended V1 Definition of Done

V1 is done when:

1. A developer can run the backend services, web apps, database, queue, and object store locally with Docker Compose, and run the desktop app natively against that local environment.
2. A user can register/login through Proveria-owned auth.
3. A user can pair a desktop app to a tenant.
4. A Tenant Admin or Producer can create a project from the desktop app.
5. A desktop user can select local files/folders and generate a signed manifest.
6. The server can validate the manifest and recompute the Merkle root.
7. A confirmed attestation becomes immutable.
8. A consumer can be authorized to a specific private attestation.
9. A consumer can submit a hash for scoped lookup.
10. Match and no-match results generate canonical JSON packages automatically.
11. Team/Enterprise result packages are Proveria-signed.
12. PDFs render server-side from canonical JSON and include QR/verification URL.
13. Free/Team/Enterprise entitlements are enforced.
14. Audit visibility follows the tiering model.
15. The desktop app can be packaged for pilot use.
16. The corporate site and portal use the same Proveria design system.

